article.headline: Cornell 58, St. Bonaventure 54
article.story: OLEAN, N.Y. (AP) -- Eric Taylor scored 17 points and pulled down eight rebounds, leading Cornell to a 58-54 win over St. Bonaventure Saturday night. It was the Big Red's first win against a Division I team this season. Lenny Collins added 14 points and nine rebounds for Cornell (2-4). Down 54-51 late in the second half, Collins made two free throws to start Cornell on a 7-0 run to end the game. Andrew Naeve capped the run with two free throws to put the Big Red up 58-54 with 3.2 seconds left. St. Bonaventure's Patrick Lottin scored 18 points and grabbed six rebounds. Willie Morse added 10 points for the Bonnies (0-5). Trailing 29-24 at halftime, Lottin made a 3-pointer from the left corner to start the Bonnies on a 15-4 run early in the second half.
